    <header>
      <h1> <span class="allcaps">How To Make:</span> Water Toast</h1>

        <p> A common recipe from the early 1900's, water toast is not considered an <i>appealing</i> meal, but stands to show human creativity with the means available to them.</p>
     </header>
      
      
   <article>  
  <section id="ingredients">
        <section>
      <h2>Ingredients</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><b>2 slices</b> dry toast</li>
        <li><b>3/4 tsp.</b> of salt</li>
        <li><b>1 cup</b> boiling water</li>
        <li><b>1/2 tbsp.</b> butter</li>
     
      </ul>
    </section>
          </article>
          
       
    <section id="instructions"> </section>
    <section>
      <h2> Instructions </h2>
      <ol>
        <li> Toast bread (via toaster, grill, etc.) </li>
        <li> Boil the cup of water and add in salt, place boiling salt water in seperate dish </li>
        <li> Dunk each piece individually in the hot water dish until sufficiently soaked </li>
        <li> Spread butter on toast </li>
        <li><s>Serve immediately</s></li>
        <li> Realize making water toast was a bad idea </li>
        <li> Dispose of immediately </li>
          
      </ol>
     </section>
          
    
    
  
